      <div class="features section">
        <div class="section__content">
          <div class="features__header">
            <h2>What is ADK-Linux?</h2>
             <h3 class="feature__body">
                An Arch Linux Based Distro with a Plasma Desktop Environment and Development Software.
              </h3>
          </div>

          <div class="features__cards">

            <div class="feature">
              <div class="feature__icon">
                <i class="far fa-window-restore"></i>
              </div>
              <h3 class="feature__header">
                Plasma Desktop
              </h3>
              <div class="feature__body">
                With Plasma the user is king. Not happy with the color scheme? Change it! Want to have your panel on the left edge of the screen? Move it! Don't like the font? Use a different one! Download custom widgets in one click and add them to your desktop or panel.
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="feature">
              <div class="feature__icon">
                <i class="fas fa-desktop"></i>
              </div>
              <h3 class="feature__header">
                Development Software
              </h3>
              <div class="feature__body">
                Developers and businesses are continually searching for solutions to make life easier as software development gains momentum and popularity throughout the market. The appropriate tools can help you get the most out of every day swiftly.
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="feature">
              <div class="feature__icon">
                <i class="fas fa-check-square"></i>
              </div>
              <h3 class="feature__header">
                Arch Linux Based
              </h3>
              <div class="feature__body">
                Arch Linux is an independently developed, x86-64 general-purpose GNU/Linux distribution that strives to provide the latest stable versions of most software by following a rolling-release model. The default installation is a minimal base system, configured by the user to only add what is purposely required.
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="wm section">
        <div class="section__content">
          <div class="wm__header">
            <h2>Plasma Desktop Theme</h2>
            <div>
              ADK-Linux uses a simple dark theme.<br>
              Based around Aritim-Dark desktop layout, or install and use any theme you wish.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="wm__cards">

            <div class="wm__entry">
              <div class="wm__image">
                <img src="assets/img/window-managers/desktop-environment-kde.svg" alt="i3" draggable=false>
              </div>

              <div class="wm__text">
                <h3 class="wm__text__title">
                  KDE Plasma <span class="wm__text__title--gray">(default)</span>
                </h3>
                <div class="wm__text__body">
                  The next generation desktop for Linux.
                </div>

                <div class="wm__theme nord">
                  <div class="wm__theme__circles">
                    <i class="circle--black fas fa-circle"></i>
                    <i class="circle--white fas fa-circle"></i>
                    <i class="circle--blue fas fa-circle"></i>
                  </div>
                  <div class="wm__theme__name">
                    Aritim-Dark
                  </div>
                </div>

              </div>
            </div>

